                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the north base of the Varadarāja Perumāḷ shrine in the Chandramauḷīśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Kulōttuṅga I. Year 3[0]: 1099-1100 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This epigraph commences with the <hi rend="italic">praśasti, Pūmādu viḷaṅga</hi>, etc., of the king.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This mentions Śeṅgāṭṭu Moḻakkan <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Marudāntakapperiyaraiyan, the <hi rend="italic">kuḍippaḷḷi</hi> of Vaḷḷaippākkam, in the eastern hamlet of [Tri]bhuvaṉamahādēvi-chaturvēdimaṅgalam in Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻa-maṇḍalam and Marudagaṇḍaṉ Marudānta . . . . . . . . . . . ., the <hi rend="italic">kuḍippaḷḷi of</hi> Veḷuṅgambāḍi of Paṉaiyūr-nāḍu. Other details are lost as the inscription is incomplete.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
